author: ArcaMax Publishing, Inc.
title: Auto review: 2024 VW Taos is blah at best | Business News | ArcaMax Publishing
text: Auto review: 2024 VW Taos is blah at best Published in [Business News](/business/businessnews/) As the Volkswagen Group has a large fleet of vehicles across its array of brands, the need for another SUV in the fleet is shocking, but in 2024 the VW Taos arrived in Grassoâ€™s Garage for a slice of the review pie. In hopes of competing with the Hyundai Kona and Kia Niro, Volkswagen delivers the Taos, a basic and plain subcompact SUV fit for five passengers with entry level options and features. It's powered by a 1.5-liter 16-valve DOHC turbo four-cylinder engine offering 158 horsepower. 4MOTION all-wheel drive was standard on our Cornflower Blue tester. The interior of the Taos was typical VW. There is a push-button start in the center console, nicely sized 10.25-inch driver instrument cluster, 19-inch black painted wheels, decently comfortable seats and good sight lines. Notably, the IQ DRIVE, VWâ€™s answer to Advance Driver Assistant Technologies, was nice and easy to use. Two-year/20,000-mile scheduled carefree maintenance was included, in addition to a four-year/50,000-mile warranty. When VW enters Grassoâ€™s Garage, we enjoy seeing what is new and exciting in the fleet. Although the Taos offers that new and exciting vibe, it seems overpriced for a basic commuter. There is no power tailgate, no memory seats and a lot of basics with no frills and thrills, which is common amongst entry level commuters. But for the $35K price tag, those should be standard options, especially in the top SEL line that we tested. I recognize the VW Tiguan and its endless success, but I'm confused as to the overall need for the Taos in the fleet. On the other hand, it's spunky, fun and roomy, and the Taos certainly looks good and has the vibe consumers enjoy, so maybe its success is here to stay, but only time will tell. 2024 Volkswagen Taos SEL 4MOTION MSRP: $33,515 MPG: 24 city / 32 highway / 26.7 as tested As Tested: $35,260 Â©2024 the Boston Herald. author: Sydney Hood
title: New autism clinic helps meet the need services in the CSRA
text: New autism clinic helps meet the need services in the CSRA AUGUSTA, Ga. (WRDW/WAGT) - A new clinic just opened in Augusta called Autism, Advocacy and Intervention. Itâ€™s an insurance-based clinic similar to a therapy office for children with diagnosed autism. Theyâ€™re the type of clinic referred to by doctors once a child is diagnosed. They work one-on-one to help autistic children meet their developmental milestones. â€œWe take for granted that we can look and talk to people and itâ€™s easy but for a lot of autistic people and children, that is not the case,â€ said Angelia Burley, a registered behavior technician for Autism, Advocacy and Intervention. Joanna May, a registered behavior technician, said: â€œRBTs are what make the clinic. Theyâ€™re the ones doing the groundwork. Theyâ€™re the ones that are on the floor with the kids every day, theyâ€™re the ones that are greeting the parents and talking to the parents.â€ The empty rooms at Autism, Advocacy and Intervention will soon provide applied behavior analysis. Burley said: â€œWe use a lot of play therapy. Thatâ€™s a big part of our success is that these kids are learning, but theyâ€™re playing. And theyâ€™re gaining new skills, and maybe some behaviors that might be difficult for parents.â€ The problem is the services are out here but itâ€™s just a matter of finding the therapists and workers to help. Dr. Karen Carter is a local developmental pediatrician. Sheâ€™s worked in Augusta for 30 years. â€œThereâ€™s just not enough people, thereâ€™s not enough therapist in our area or in any other area. Itâ€™s pretty critical,â€ said Carter. â€œSometimes itâ€™s a very long waiting list. Recently, I had a child in the clinic and we did all the right things we did. We did the right evaluations, we did the right paperwork, and we sent it to the insurance company. And we still couldnâ€™t get the Applied Behavioral Analysis for a year.â€ Dr. Carter said the earlier the intervention, the better the outcomes. May said: â€œThe more clinics there are, that are offering ABA services, the more availability there is to the community to have those services met without having to be on these long waitlists.â€ To learn more about Autism, Advocacy and Intervention, [visit their website](https://autismai.com/). author: amarylisa-gonsalves
title: Justin Bieber receives support from fans after his hollow-eyed photos spark marital problems rumours with
text:
Table of Contents
Justin Bieber has been making headlines recently for his relationship with his wife Hailey Bieber. While the singer has been off the charts for some time now and has been facing health issues, the internet has theories that his relationship with his wife could be strained. To add to it, his latest appearance in New York City on Wednesday raised more eyebrows as he looked visibly tense and hollow-eyed. His condition further fueled the speculations about potential marital issues with his wife. Notably, this comes after the parents to Jack Blues Bieber were spotted recently during a date night together over the weekend.
However, fans and users on the internet have come out in support of the Baby singer.
Justin Bieber spotted looking hollow-eyed in New York
The Kiss Me singer was spotted in New York sporting wearing his signature dishevelled-chic look, with a bright yellow hoodie, baggy cargo pants, and fuzzy slipper-like shoes. The singer was seen walking through the bustling streets of New York City when his dramatic gesture of grabbing his crotch grabbed eyeballs.
He was also seen wearing a black baseball cap as walked towards his luxury SUV parked around the corner. Meanwhile, Hailey was spotted leaving a building in Union Square all alone.
Their separate appearances come after recent rumours of a tumultuous marriage. It started when Bieber unfollowed his wife on Instagram leading to a sea of speculations. However, he later clarified on his Instagram stories saying, â€œSomeone went on my account and unfollowed my wife. Shit is getting suss out here.â€
Fans support Justin
However, the internet stood in support of the Mistletoe singer noting that he was a father to a newborn baby and that it was natural for him to be sleep-deprived thus causing the hollow eyes.
One user sarcastically noted, â€œMan, have you ever seen a sleep-deprived first-time father? We all look like that.â€ Another user defended him saying, â€œHeâ€™s had lime disease and a new baby leave him alone mxâ€
Other users noted things like, â€œHeâ€™s a new daddy, cut him some slack. Heâ€™s like, â€œI havenâ€™t slept in 4 years,â€ â€œHis baby not even 1 yet. That nigga jus tired asf ðŸ˜­â€. Another fan wrote, â€œThe man told yall he was dealing with an illness if not last year the year before. Let that baby live in peace.â€
Justin Bieber and Hailey Bieber have been married for around six years now. They welcomed their first child in August 2024, a boy who they named Jack Blues Bieber.
